  "body": "The export control node popup does not resize on MacOs to accommodate a list with multiple synced devices.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1782\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-09-14 at 15 51 55\" src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/47811206/aee4c326-1208-4bcc-9474-733b7138de6f\">\r\n\r\nRepro steps:\r\n1. Make sure you have multiple devices in the sync list (Usually it's enough to login into the same account from multiple app versions)\r\n2. Create a new community or open one that you own\r\n3. Go to community settings\r\n4. Click `How to move control node`\r\n\r\nExpected behaviour:\r\nA popup is opened containing a list of synced devices. The popup should be as large as possible to accommodate the list. Whenever there is no space left for the popup to grow, the synced devices list should become scrollable.\r\n\r\nActual behaviour:\r\nThe popup size is constant and only 1 device is visible from the list. The list is scrollable.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nCan be reproduced on MacOs only (Qt 5.15.8 for arm64)\r\nCannot be reproduced on Storybook\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @alexjba in https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/12131#discussion_r1325901025_\r\n            ",
